text: Péter Bakosi (born 23 June 1993) is a Hungarian high jumper. He finished eighth at the 2012 World Junior Championships, and fifth at the 2015 European U23 Championships. He also competed at the 2013 European U23 Championships, the 2015 European Indoor Championships and the 2017 European Indoor Championships without reaching the final. His personal best jump is 2.26 metres, achieved in July 2016 in Miskolc. ==References== Category:1993 births Category:Living people Category:Hungarian male high jumpers Category:European Games competitors for Hungary Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 2019 European Games Category:Hungarian Athletics Championships winners
